observations.recommendation:
Management advice the Municipal Accountant to: 
a.Coordinate with the Municipal Treasurer and the implementing offices of the DOH & DILG funded projects and return to the source agencies the balance of fund transferred with corresponding completed programs or projects pursuant to item 4.9 of COA Circular No. 94 – 013;

b.Clarify/verify with the RHU and/or Philhealth and BFP personnel whether the program undertakings with the source agency covering the depository accounts maintained by the LGU are still active and continue to be implemented, else, the balances will be returned to the SA and close the depository accounts.  Ensure that the said program undertakings will be supported with MOA; 

c.Return to the SA the balance of the fund transfer from the DAR-IFAD which was already phased out; and

d.Conduct regular close monitoring of the status on the individual subsidiary ledger accounts composing the Due to NGAs account to avoid misrepresentation of the accounts in the FS.

We recommended that the Management: 

a.	Direct the Municipal Engineer and Municipal Planning and Development Officer to review and expedite execution of priority projects included in the Annual Investment Plan so that delay in the implementation thereof could be avoided and desired benefits may be derived accordingly; and

b.	Prepare a realistic and implementable plan, after taking into consideration all the technical aspects and funding requirements in the implementation, to avoid re – programming and fast track the project implementation;

The Management advise the Municipal Accountant to:

Revert to the General Fund, with the assistance of the Municipal Treasurer, the unexpended LGU Counterparts/Equity and of which the corresponding projects had already been already been completed with subject amount of P336,674.12 to be used for priority local government programs and projects of the Municipality;

Continue to trace back and identify the source agency of the project construction of Sr. Citizen Building and return the unexpended balance of  P22,819.00. When the amount  is proven free from any obligation, revert the amount to the General Fund to be used for priority local government programs and projects of the LGU;

Verify if the programs/projects DA- SELAP (NO.11) to the 1st  Tranche for the Primary Care Revitalized  (No. 19), were complete or on-going. Conduct extensive effort to identify the source agency of the Programs/projects that were deficient of information. With the assistance of the Municipal Treasurer, return to the source agency the balance of the complete programs/project;

Conduct regular monitoring of the status on the individual subsidiary ledger accounts composing the due to NGAs account to avoid misrepresentation of the accounts in the FS.

We recommended the management to:

a.	Request an authority from the Source Agency for extended utilization of the fund and once approved, immediately utilize for intended purpose, otherwise, return the unutilized funds to the  source agencies;

b.	Instruct the Municipal Accountant to update her records, conduct a thorough review of the affected accounts to determine the cause of non-reconciliation and non-moving balances, initiate corrections/ adjustments and thereafter come up with all accounts in their correct balances, so that accounts will be fairly  presented in the financial statements;

c.	Exert extra effort to retrieve the documents of unidentified accounts or those without details in the subsidiary ledgers to properly classify the accounts recorded; and


d.	Fast track the implementation of the PPAs funded by those fund transfers from other agencies, so the benefits that will be derived from the project will be afforded immediately to the intended beneficiaries

We recommended that Management strictly comply with the following:

 a. Submit the lacking documentary requirements;

 b. Submit written explanations and/or justifications on why the violations were committed;

 c. Avoid procuring goods that were not included in the APP and in the supplemental procurement plans; and

 d. Ensure that future procurement of land should be in accordance with the IRR of RA 10752 and with Section 13.1 of COA Circular 2012-001.

7.7	We recommended that management:
1.	Strictly adhere to the provision of Section 5 of DILG-DBM JMC                 No. 2017-1 dated February 22, 2017 to ensure the optimal utilization of 20 percent DF to help achieve the desirable socio-economic and environmental management outcomes of the municipality;
2.	Mobilize the concerned offices in the early planning and implementation of development projects to avoid incurring possible additional cost as a result of delayed implementation;
3.	Inform the intended beneficiaries of the programmed projects so that proper coordination will facilitate in the execution of the projects and the benefits thereof at the earliest possible time; and
4.	Prepare a catch up plan and fast tract the implementation of the above-mentioned priority development projects.
